For your Grammy consideration in the Traditional Blues category. First round voting ends October 10 at 6 PM.

October 8, 2019 – King Biscuit Blues Festival And Pinetop Homecoming This Week!

It’s time to pass the biscuits once again. Bob Corritore gathers with friends down south to play a few shows and enjoy some southern hospitality! Saturday, October 12 King Biscuit Blues Festival, Helena, Arkansas, main stage 4pm Bob makes a guest appearance with the Andy T Band featuring Alabama Mike and Anson Funderburgh. For full fest lineup, click here.

Sunday, October 13 Pinetop Homecoming, Hopson’s Plantation, Clarksdale, Mississippi, a set with the Bobs Of The Blues (Bob Margolin, Bob Stroger, Bob Corritore). This show honors the Pinetop Perkins Foundation.

September 30, 2019 – Shows Thursday In Phoenix And Saturday In Chicago!

Click the flyers below for more information and tickets.

September 25, 2019 – Bob’s Birthday Party And CD Release Party!

It’s a double celebration this Saturday night at the Rhythm Room! Bob Corritore celebrates his birthday and the release of Bob Corritore & Friends/Do The Hip-Shake Baby! Bob Corritore will perform alongside many special guests including Alabama Mike, Oscar Wilson, The Fremonts, Bill Howl-N-Madd Perry & Shy Perry, Jimi Primetime Smith, Adriana Marie & L.A. Jones, Brian Fahey, Johnny Rapp, and Yahni Riley. Doors at 7pm music starting at 8pm. Gonna be a party! For tickets click here.

September 9, 2019 – Blues Blast Music Awards This Friday Plus A Party On Thursday At The Old Chess Records Building!

Bob Corritore will appear on Friday, September 13 at the Blues Blast Music Awards in Rockford, IL. The 2018 album Bob Corritore & Friends/Don’t Let The Devil Ride is up for Traditional Blues Album! Bob also participated on a few songs for Tony Holiday’s Porch Sessions which is up for Best Live Recording. Bob’s revue set will feature vocalists Oscar Wilson and Tail Dragger, guitarist Mojo Mark Cihlar, and the great Doug Demming & The Jewel Tones. Gonna be a fun night filled with great performances!

The night before, on Thursday, September 12 there is a bash at Willie Dixon’s Blues Heaven Foundation headquarters at the old Chess Records Studio, 2120 S. Michigan Ave., Chicago. Tail Dragger and Bob Corritore will guest with John Primer’s Real Deal Blues Band – which features harmonica ace Steve Bell! On display that night will be the fantastic photography of Eric Kriesant.

Bob Corritore & Friends/Don’t Let The Devil Ride is nominated in the Traditional Blues Album category. Anyone can vote!

July 31, 2019 – John Primer & Bob Corritore Perform This Sunday At Calgary Blues Festival

John Primer and Bob Corritore with the amazing rhythm section of Bob Stroger and Kenny “Beedy Eyes” Smith will perform a set of straight-ahead Chicago blues at the Calgary Blues Festival this Sunday, Aug 4. Check out the fantastic festival lineup on the poster below.

For more info and to buy tickets: www.calgarybluesfest.com

Voting is going on right now! Voting ends August 16. You can vote at this link. Thanks!

July 22, 2019 – All-Star Blues Showcase This Friday at Rhythm Room

July 19, 2019 – William Clarke Collectors LP Compiled By Bob Corritore Available Now On Bear Family!

When Germany’s famed Bear Family Records asked Bob Corritore to help compile a collectors limited edition LP by late West Coast harmonica master William Clarke, the answer was an absolute yes! Bob worked closely with William’s widow Jeanette to carefully choose the 10 wonderful songs and to get inside perspective from which to write the liner notes. Bear Family records is known as an industry leader for its flawless production. The end result is for you to judge. For more info and to order, click here.

July 15, 2019 – Today Is The Last Day To Vote In The Living Blues Awards

Today is the last day to vote for the Living Blues Awards. Bob Corritore is nominated in the Harmonica category!

Please go to www.livingblues.com to place your votes!

Bob Corritore is nominated for a Living Blues Award in the Harmonica category. Voting ends July 15.

Please participate in the voting process at www.livingblues.com.

Bob Corritore, Henry Gray, and John Primer are all nominated for Living Blues Awards!

July 2, 2019 – Voting Is Open Now For The 2019 Blues Blast Music Awards!

Voting is now open for the Blues Blast Music Awards. Anyone can vote at www.bluesblastmagazine.com. Bob Corritore & Friends / Don’t Let The Devil Ride is up for Traditional Blues Album! Please vote your choices today!

And also please remember to vote in the Living Blues Awards which closes on July 15. Bob Corritore is up for an award in the Harmonica Category! Voting at www.livingblues.com.

June 24, 2019 – The Dave Riley / Bob Corritore Juke Joint Blues Band This Saturday at The Rhythm Room

June 19, 2019 – Nominations, Reviews, Accolades

Bob Corritore has been very active lately, and the media and blues scene seems to be noticing. Bob recently was nominated for a Living Blues award in the Harmonica category, and a Blues Blast Music Award for The 2018 Traditional Blues Album for Bob Corritore & Friends/Don’t Let The Devil Ride.

His 2019 release Bob Corritore & Friends/Do The Hip-Shake Baby! recently got rave reviews in DownBeat Magazine (4 stars!) and Living Blues, as well as a multitude of other noted publications!

Bob also has guest appearances on some high profile albums: Tony Holiday/Porch Sessions, released earlier this year (and up for a Blues Blues Blast Music Award), and soon to be released albums Zac Harmon/Mississippi BarBQ and Ben Levin/Before Me. And Harmonica.com did a feature interview and Bob earlier this year! Thank you VizzTone Label Group and Brat Girl Media for getting the word out!

Living Blues Awards voting going on now! Place your votes today at www.LivingBlues.com.

Blues Blast Music Awards voting begins July 1st at www.BluesBlastMagazine.com.

May 22, 2019 – Chico Chism Memorial Birthday Celebration This Saturday At The Rhythm Room

Each year we remember the great Chico Chism, who lived in the last 20 years of his life as a true blessing of the Phoenix blues scene!

We celebrate Chico Chism this Saturday, 7pm doors, 8pm music, at the Rhythm Room, 1019 E. Indian School Road in Phoenix.

Bill Tarsha & his Rocket 88s are the host band and some of the special guests include Hans Olson, Dave Riley, Jimi “Primetime” Smith, Bob Corritore, Brian Fahey, Johnny Rapp, Yahni Riley, Elgin, Gypsy Wild At Harp, Elizabeth Greene, Walking Cane Mark, Country Soul Bob, Charles Mack, George Vaught & The Flamekeepers, Paul Klapper, Smokestack Lightning, and more!

Chico was an integral part of the Rhythm Room community and we honor him this Saturday!

May 2, 2019 – Bob Corritore & Friends / Do The Hip Shake Baby To Be Released Tomorrow On Friday, May 3!

To pre-order click http://lnk.to/hipshake.

Many thanks to all the DJs, reviewers and fans who have boosted this new release! Many thanks to the long list of fantastic musicians who all contributed their heartfelt performances to this project. And special thanks to Clarke Rigsby, John Wroble, and Kid Andersen who were behind the scenes heroes in the making of this record. And of course we must acknowledge the team over at VizzTone Label Group and BratGirl Media for their amazing efforts in the release and promotion of this album! Order today and it will be shipped tomorrow!

Harpist/vocalist Tony Holiday traveled across the country to record with his favorite blues musicians in informal, spirited performance situations. This album brilliantly provides a snapshot exemplifying today’s traditional blues as seen through the eyes of this young keeper of the flame. Congratulations Tony Holiday!

January 19, 2019 – Happy 94th Birthday To Henry Gray!

Blues piano legend Henry Gray is celebrating his 94th birthday today at his home in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. Henry is simply the greatest blues piano player alive today, and is one of the few remaining links to the original Chicago blues of the late 40s and early 1950s! He played on numerous classic records with Howlin’ Wolf, Jimmy Rogers, Jimmy Reed, Little Walter, Billy Boy Arnold and others. His recent performance last October at the Crescent City Blues Festival showed us that Henry is still at the top of this game! Happy 94th birthday Henry Gray!
